A murder case of Marumpho Charles who has been accused of hacking his brother to death will be back again in court on June 28.Charles was granted a R1000 bail at the Thabamoopo Magistrate&#8217;s Court, Limpopo, on Tuesday.Limpopo police spokesperson Colonel Motshe Ngoepe said the two brothers had been engaged in a domestic fight, when the other brother hacked to death his sibling with an axe. The two brothers had a domestic dispute when the incident happened. Police arrested him on the same day, Ngoepe said.-TNA Reporter&nbsp;